<subSubSection id="55468C5836AA3C3BF50E9B079713371B" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="conservation status">
<paragraph id="44FCE19021D344C72CBB6F44E21FC882" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Conservation status in Cameroon.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B8C61C29928AAB698A5174C8A4E3E67C" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName id="36C6CEEDEA3CC80444EC4D861FCFC216" authorityName="C. Cusset ex Cheek, Pl Mount Oku &amp; Ijim Ridge, Cameroon, Conserv. Checklist 153" authorityYear="2000" baseAuthorityName="G. Taylor" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Podostemaceae" genus="Saxicolella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Saxicolella marginalis" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marginalis">
<emphasis id="A240826C8A846E922A3C2952B8FBED9D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Saxicolella marginalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is listed on http://www.iucnredlist.org. The taxon has been assessed globally as Critically Endangered (
<bibRefCitation id="61608BE94E8094352F4799330A6BC831" author="Ouedraogo, L" journalOrPublisher="Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" refId="B68" refString="Ouedraogo, L, 2010b. Saxicolellamarginalis. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2010: e.T39742A10261941. [Downloaded on 20 August 2018]" title="Saxicolellamarginalis. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2010: e. T 39742 A 10261941. [Downloaded on 20 August 2018]" year="2010 b">Ouedraogo 2010b</bibRefCitation>
). There is only one known collecting locality in the country. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="116DB80C77F470F33C266C9D7F7D7D78" author="Ouedraogo, L" journalOrPublisher="Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" refId="B68" refString="Ouedraogo, L, 2010b. Saxicolellamarginalis. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2010: e.T39742A10261941. [Downloaded on 20 August 2018]" title="Saxicolellamarginalis. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2010: e. T 39742 A 10261941. [Downloaded on 20 August 2018]" year="2010 b">Ouedraogo (2010b)</bibRefCitation>
there is decline in the quality of the habitat due to pollution from laundry operations in the town of Fundong upstream of the site of this species. Based on this threat the assessment of Critically Endangered is maintained. IUCN Red List Category: 
<emphasis id="B168F27891381A04C59A9627C87BA594" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Critically Endangered B1ab (iii) +2ab (iii)</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
